From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ws63-rs <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 11 Jun 2026 10:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] hw/riscv: register the HiSilicon BS20 machine (minimal/M1)

Build-system integration for hw/riscv/bs20.c (the minimal BS20 / BS2X machine).
Like bs21.c/bs22.c, bs20.c reuses the shared HiSilicon riscv31 device models from
ws63.c via hisi_riscv31.h, so CONFIG_BS20 selects CONFIG_WS63.

BS20 shares the BS2X peripheral bases (platform_core.h) + IRQ numbers
(chip_core_irq.h) with BS21E/BS22, but has a smaller 128K L2RAM (vs 160K) — so
unlike bs22 (byte-identical to bs21), BS20 is genuinely distinct: its -m bank is
128K, and the bs20 firmware (examples/bs20) ships a matching 128K memory.x (stack
top 0x120000) rather than the 160K layout (stack top 0x128000), which would
overflow the bank.

Adds the CONFIG_BS20 meson source entry and the Kconfig symbol (default y on
RISCV32, selects UNIMP + WS63). Registers `-M bs20`.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 hw/riscv/Kconfig     | 7 +++++++
 hw/riscv/meson.build | 1 +
 2 files changed, 8 insertions(+)
diff --git a/hw/riscv/Kconfig b/hw/riscv/Kconfig
--- a/hw/riscv/Kconfig
+++ b/hw/riscv/Kconfig
@@ -139,3 +139,10 @@
     depends on RISCV32
     select UNIMP
     select WS63
+
+config BS20
+    bool
+    default y
+    depends on RISCV32
+    select UNIMP
+    select WS63
diff --git a/hw/riscv/meson.build b/hw/riscv/meson.build
--- a/hw/riscv/meson.build
+++ b/hw/riscv/meson.build
@@ -17,4 +17,5 @@
 riscv_ss.add(when: 'CONFIG_WS63', if_true: files('ws63.c'))
 riscv_ss.add(when: 'CONFIG_BS21', if_true: files('bs21.c'))
 riscv_ss.add(when: 'CONFIG_BS22', if_true: files('bs22.c'))
+riscv_ss.add(when: 'CONFIG_BS20', if_true: files('bs20.c'))
 hw_arch += {'riscv': riscv_ss}
